meta.name: I'm a Celebrity, Get Me Out of Here!
meta.description: I'm a Celebrity, Get Me Out of Here! is the country's top survival reality TV show, where celebrities must live without any comforts and compete against each other in order to be crowned winner.

videos.title: I'm A Celebrity…Get Me Out Of Here! Coming Out
videos.overview: Ant and Dec presents the best bits from the latest series, with cameras following each contestant as they journey out of the jungle and to their luxury hotel on Australia's Gold Coast, where they reveal what they really thought of their fellow campmates. The cast also reunite to share behind-the-scenes stories and reminisce about their time in camp, while there is an interview with the newly crowned King or Queen of the Jungle celebrates their victory and return to reality.

Episode 1
videos.overview: I'm A Celebrity…Get Me Out Of Here! is back which can mean only one thing… the time has come for a brand new cast of celebrities to head down under and battle it out in TV's toughest challenge.This year's fresh batch of celebrities will be thrown in at the deep end, as they all face gruelling challenges right from the start, as viewers choose which of them will face the first Bushtucker Trial.

videos.title: Episode 2
videos.overview: With their lives of luxury far behind them, the celebrities settle into camp life. But who will be next to face the Bushtucker Trial? Ant and Dec present all the latest action from the jungle.

videos.title: Episode 3
videos.overview: The surprises keep on coming in the jungle as the celebrities struggle to adapt to life in camp. Ant and Dec present all the latest action from down under.

videos.title: Episode 4

videos.overview: With no excuses now, every celebrity should have settled into camp life. But who will be next to face the Bushtucker Trial? Ant and Dec deliver the bad news to one of the celebs.

videos.overview: As the celebrities settle into their second week in the jungle, the competition is hotting up. Who is working hard for the good of camp - and who is in it for themselves? Ant and Dec present the latest updates.

videos.title: Episode 9
videos.overview: With camp relying on every Bushtucker Trial for food, who is crumbling under the pressure, who is adapting to jungle life and who is missing their home comforts? Ant and Dec round up all the latest from down under.

videos.title: Episode 10
videos.overview: The surprises continue for the celebrities, as the pressure really mounts in camp. Ant and Dec round up all the latest from the jungle.

videos.title: Episode 13

videos.title: Episode 14
videos.overview: Two weeks in, which of the campmates has what it takes to be crowned King or Queen of the Jungle?

videos.title: Episode 15
videos.overview: As the campmates face the prospect of returning to their celebrity lifestyles, who's ready to leave the jungle and who's desperate to stay?

videos.title: Episode 16
videos.overview: The celebrities battle hunger, the jungle and each other as the title of King or Queen of the Jungle gets closer for one of them.

videos.title: Episode 17
videos.overview: The celebrities are hungry and missing home, but they still need to win food for camp in the Bushtucker Trial.

videos.title: Episode 18
videos.overview: The celebrities face another day of hardship and hunger in the jungle, but the finish line is finally in sight.

videos.title: Episode 19
videos.overview: The competition is ramping up and jungle life isn't getting any easier, but who has their sights set on the Jungle Crown?

videos.title: Semi Final
videos.overview: The remaining campmates all have their eyes on the prize, but who will fall at the final hurdle in the race to be crowned this year's King or Queen of the Jungle?

videos.title: Final
videos.overview: They've survived the Bushtucker Trials, camp life and their fellow celebrities, but which of the finalists will you crown this year's King or Queen of the Jungle?

videos.title: I'm A Celebrity...Get Me Out Of Here! Coming Out
videos.overview: I'm A Celebrity… Get Me Out Of Here! Coming Out follows this year's celebrities from the moment they step foot off the legendary bridge, to the emotional reunions with their family and friends.The show captures their reactions as they spend their first night back in luxury. As they prepare to wash the Jungle out of their hair, how will they cope going back to life in the outside world?

videos.title: Coming Out
videos.overview: For weeks, viewers and the world's media alike watched as 11 celebrities were stripped of all comfort and dumped in the Australian Jungle where they survived with no contact from the outside world, completing trials and challenges to stave off hunger. Now, they return to the lap of luxury and we have exclusive access as they settle back into the world they left behind.

videos.title: Episode 1
videos.overview: I'm a Celebrity returns with a new set of celebrity campmates ready to take on the jungle.

videos.title: Episode 2
videos.overview: The celebrities are settling in - but will they win stars in the first Bushtucker Trial?

videos.title: Episode 3
videos.overview: The celebs struggle to adjust to jungle life as the fight for stars and food continues.

videos.title: Episode 4
videos.overview: Anything could happen as the campmates take on Bushtucker trials to keep hunger at bay.

videos.title: Episode 5
videos.overview: The surprises keep on coming as the campmates battle for food and stars.

videos.title: Episode 6
videos.overview: Who will face the next Bushtucker Trial?

videos.title: Episode 7
videos.overview: After a week in the jungle, the campmates are starting to feel tired and hungry - but this time, all of them are set to face the latest Bushtucker Trial. With Ian Wright in particular suffering from a lack of food, and the camps still split in two, will they be able to summon up the strength to secure a good feed this evening?

videos.title: Episode 8
videos.overview: Seven days into their jungle experience, things step up a gear for the campmates as Ian Wright and Jacqueline Jossa undertake tonight's Bushtucker Trial - Crevice of Cruelty. Plus, highlights of the past 24 hours.

videos.title: Episode 9
videos.overview: Tired, hungry, and missing their loved ones, the campmates have to keep one another's morale up as they find out who will face the next Bushtucker Trial. Ant and Dec also present round-up of all the goings-on over the past 24 hours.

videos.title: Episode 10
videos.overview: Andrew Maxwell takes on the Ark of Agony Bushtucker Trial having raised the hackles of the general public during his argument with Ian Wright. The morale of the campmates has been boosted thanks to their care packages from home and, in most cases, a much-needed roast dinner, but winning as many stars as possible will help to keep up the spirits for further challenges to come.

videos.title: Episode 11
videos.overview: The latest Bushtucker Trial is Deadly Dungeon, in which Ian Wright and James Haskell are the two celebrities charged with winning food for the others, while the latest leader of the camp and their deputy also take their positions after being voted for by the general public.

videos.title: Episode 12
videos.overview: Jacqueline Jossa, Roman Kemp, Ian Wright and Nadine Coyle take on the Sinister Circus in the first of 'The Reckonings' challenges. The choice of Caitlyn Jenner and Andy Whyment as leader and deputy leader of the camp seems to have gone down well, but tension between Ian Wright and Andrew Maxwell has created something of an atmosphere, which won't be helped if the celebs don't get a good meal once again.

videos.title: Episode 13
videos.overview: The fight for immunity from being voted off is under way with the celebrities facing further challenges to ensure their stay in the jungle continues for a little while longer. Six of the campmates went without a proper meal last night after losing out to the other celebs in The Reckonings, leaving them hungry, yet determined to put that right this time.

videos.title: Episode 14
videos.overview: Ant and Dec host the latest episode of the celebrity survival challenge, with the campmates adjusting to life without Adele Roberts, who was the first person to be voted off. Ian Wright, James Haskell and Myles Stephenson were immune from the vote-off last time, but there's no such safety net now, and their place is in the jungle is under threat.

videos.title: Episode 15
videos.overview: As the campmates face being booted out of the jungle back into their life of luxury, who is ready to make that jump and who wants to stay another day? Presented by Ant and Dec.

videos.title: Episode 16
videos.overview: Ant and Dec host the celebrity survival challenge, which sees a group of famous faces living in the Australian jungle, struggling to complete the tough daily tasks and dreaded Bushtucker Trials. The campmates are tired, hungry and homesick, but need to keep winning stars - and food - if they are going to make it to the end.

videos.title: Episode 17
videos.overview: Ant and Dec host the celebrity survival challenge, which sees a group of famous faces living in the Australian jungle, struggling to complete the tough daily tasks and dreaded Bushtucker Trials. The campmates are tired, hungry and homesick, but need to keep winning stars - and food - if they are going to make it to the end.

videos.title: Episode 18
videos.overview: Ant and Dec present the celebrity survival challenge, which sees a group of famous faces living in the Australian jungle, struggling to complete the tough daily tasks and dreaded Bushtucker Trials. Caitlyn Jenner has proved to be one of this year's most popular contestants, but it's anyone's guess who has the staying power to make it through to the final.

videos.title: Episode 19
videos.overview: The competition is getting tougher as the celebrity campmates get closer to one of them being crowned King or Queen of the Jungle. Ant and Dec present the highlights of the past 24 hours around the camp fire. With assorted challenges testing the contestants, and homesickness taking its toll, tensions are running high, but with the end in sight, the stars try to keep their eyes on the prize.

videos.title: Episode 20
videos.overview: Ant and Dec provide coverage of the latest stage in the celebrity survival challenge, which sees a group of famous faces living in the Australian jungle, struggling to complete the tough daily tasks and dreaded Bushtucker Trials in a bid to be crowned King or Queen of the Jungle. Which of them will start to crack under the pressure?

videos.title: Episode 21
videos.overview: Ant and Dec present the celebrity challenge, as the famous faces' ordeal in the Australian jungle draws close to its conclusion. The pair offer viewers one last chance to catch up with the remaining contestants, all of whom will have their hearts set on being named King or Queen of the Jungle.

videos.title: Episode 22
videos.overview: They've survived until the end after enduring Bushtucker Trials, camp life and each other. But which of the finalists will you crown this year's King or Queen of the Jungle? Ant and Dec reveal which of the campmates will follow in the footsteps of 2018 winner Harry Redknapp. It's been a rollercoaster ride of a contest, with highlights including the windy skyscraper challenge on day one, and the moment Jacqueline Jossa had to face her fear of spiders in an early challenge. While Caitlyn Jenner has become a show favourite, it remains to be seen who will emerge from the camp victorious.

videos.title: Coming Out
videos.overview: Just a few days after the new King or Queen of the jungle was crowned, Ant and Dec present the usual round-up of what happened behind the scenes as each campmate was voted out. From the first to the last, the programme reveals what they get up to in their first few days of freedom, and captures their reactions to old rivals and trusted friends, while their families gather for emotional reunions with their loved ones.

videos.title: Episode 1
videos.overview: For the first time in its history, Ant and Dec host the show in the UK. But what will they make of their new home, Gwrych Castle in Abergele on the North Wales coast?

videos.title: Episode 2
videos.overview: The famous faces get used to life in their new surroundings at Gwrych Castle in Abergele on the north Wales coast as they take part in the trials to try to win food for everyone. Ant and Dec oversee proceedings.

videos.title: Episode 3
videos.overview: Gwrych Castle is a far cry from the heat of the Australian jungle, as the contestants discover while adjusting to life on the north Wales coast. As ever, Ant and Dec will be bringing viewers up to date on the latest developments as the trials continue. Will any of the celebrities decide to go home early, or will they stay the course?

videos.title: Episode 4
videos.overview: Day four and contestants continue to cope with life at Gwrych Castle. As usual there has been plenty of drama over the past 24 hours, and Ant and Dec give us the lowdown on some of the highs and lows, as well as dropping more bombshells for those hungry celebrities.

videos.title: Episode 5
videos.overview: While the regular I'm A Celebrity crew in New South Wales take a break this year, closer to home in north Wales, contestants are wishing they had some Australian sun as the latest challenges unfold. Ant and Dec bring viewers up to speed on the latest developments at Gwrych Castle as those fiendish tasks test the mettle of the famous, and not so famous, contestants.

videos.title: Episode 6
videos.overview: With the first week in the castle nearly over, the campmates continue to battle the elements in the hope of winning stars for camp. Ant and Dec monitor events, helping set tasks and challenges along the way.

videos.title: Episode 7
videos.overview: On day seven in the Welsh camp, the celebrities are trying to keep body and soul together while the weather tests their mettle. Ant and Dec take a look back at all the best bits from the first week, along with some exclusive unseen moments.

videos.title: Episode 14
videos.overview: After two weeks at the castle, the contestants have endured all manner of tasks and ordeals, but the end is in sight. As ever, Ant and Dec guide viewers through highlights from the past 24 hours, and look ahead to the next stage.

videos.title: Episode 15
videos.overview: The celebrities have endured two weeks of castle life, and they continue to battle it out in the quest to be crowned winner of the 2020 contest. Ant and Dec present.

videos.title: Episode 16
videos.overview: With the final on the horizon, the remaining contestants keep their eyes on the prize. Plus, Ant and Dec reflect on the past 24 hours in the Welsh camp, and look ahead to the next tasks.

videos.title: Episode 17
videos.overview: With more trials and challenges thrown their way, the celebrities continue to brave life in the castle. Ant and Dec present some of the highlights of the past 24 hours and look forward to the next stage, while all eyes are on Friday's final.

videos.title: Episode 18
videos.overview: Day 18 at the Welsh castle, and while contestants keep their eyes on the prize, Ant and Dec present highlights from the past 24 hours. Plus, a look at some of the tasks to come.

videos.title: Episode 19
videos.overview: The campmates continue to battle the elements and their hunger in north Wales as the finale approaches. Ant and Dec examine highlights from the past 24 hours, and look ahead to that all-important conclusion when the King or Queen of the Castle will be announced.

videos.title: Episode 20
videos.overview: It's the final, and after three weeks of facing their fears, coping with hunger and battling the elements, Ant and Dec reveal who will be crowned King or Queen of the Castle.

videos.title: Episode 1
videos.overview: Ant and Dec present the celebrity survival challenge, and after two years in Wales they are back in Australia, where a fresh batch of famous faces will be waving goodbye to their lives of luxury and set up camp in the jungle for up to three weeks, battling bugs and Bushtucker Trials, rations and rain, and heat and hunger. After three weeks, one of them will eventually emerge as this year's King or Queen of the Jungle, taking the crown from reigning champion Danny Miller of Emmerdale.

videos.title: Episode 1

Life in the jungle is proving to be a taxing experience for some, while others take it in their stride. At least two major factors weigh on all of their minds - will they have enough to eat, and who will follow in the footsteps of Danny Jones, winner of the 2024 series?

It remains to be seen whether the latest batch of contestants will do better than the 2024 team.
